ce:section.ce:para:
Zeta potential is an important indicator of the stability of colloidal dispersion system. We conducted separate measurements of the Zeta potential of Pf-CDs and ENR solution under pH 7 conditions. The results showed that before mixing ENR with Pf-CDs, both had Zeta potentials of −5.36 mV and 4.66 mV, respectively (

                           Fig. S7

                        ). The individual solutions had a tendency to coagulate or aggregate, but after being mixed, the Zeta potential of the entire system increased to −11.3 mV, indicating that the particles in the mixed solution system tend to spread apart or dissolve. This outcome may be due to the formation of intermolecular hydrogen bonds between the C-F [43] or C = O in the ENR structure and the amides in Pf-CDs, thereby preventing interactions between ENR molecules [44].
